@node history "Harlot V1.04; History"

/*
** History:
**
** The story so far:
**
**  After exhaustive stress testing over the last couple of days I have
** noticed a few things about the Workbench environment and how Harlot
** interacts.  The first thing that I noticed was that when you select Last
** Message from the menu's it displays nothing, this, I assume is because
** the last message field is in the window structure - which of-course
** isn't WB's...
**  The second and final thing was that when selecting ResetWB from the
** menus the Workbench menus appear to be deallocated, and then
** reallocated, which could lead to an unstable system.
**  Also, just a guess, each LendMenu() causes the system to allocate
** approximately 50bytes of memory.
**
** V1.00	05/04/96	 Started coding an idea which would
**				revolutionise the computing industry
** V1.01			 Became sidetracked and made Harlot attach
**				to ALL windows without menus
** V1.02	06/04/96	 Rewrote the code in C to make it easier to
**				build.
** V1.03	(Released)	 Noticed something strange with the
**				arguments for LendMenus(), the compiler
**				must be switching them.
** V1.04	10/04/96	 Removed lots of redundant code
**		(Released)	 Added an option to allow the system
**				friendly removal of harlot menus.
**				 Removed the printf() statements, replacing
**				them with my own SMALL routine, dropped the
**				size down by over 2000bytes
*/

@endnode
